  "prompt": "What is the meaning of \u0e17\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e16\u0e23\u0e23\u0e1e\u0e4c?",
  "response": "The term \"\u0e17\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e16\u0e23\u0e23\u0e1e\u0e4c\" is Thai and can be translated to \"cursed gold\" or \"enchanted gold\" in English. It typically refers to gold that is believed to have supernatural properties or be associated with a curse. In Thai culture and folklore, objects like gold can be subject to magical enchantments or curses, making \"\u0e17\u0e2d\u0e07\u0e2d\u0e32\u0e16\u0e23\u0e23\u0e1e\u0e4c\" a concept where the gold could bring misfortune or strange occurrences to its owner. This term can be found in stories, myths, and legends.",
